# UI buttons and crawl actions

Canonical skill: [`ai/skills/react-inertia-frontend/SKILL.md`](../../ai/skills/react-inertia-frontend/SKILL.md)

## Buttons

- Use [`Button`](resources/js/Components/Button.tsx) or [`ActionButton`](resources/js/Components/ActionButton.tsx) for interactive controls.
- Do **not** add raw `rounded-md bg-*` button classes in pages or feature components.
- Semantic variants live in [`buttonVariants.ts`](resources/js/lib/buttonVariants.ts):
  - `primary` — main form submit / confirm
  - `primaryDark` — strong CTA (filters, modal confirm)
  - `secondary` — neutral outline
  - `connect` — OAuth / connect
  - `destructive` — disconnect / delete
  - `warning` — reauthorize
  - `ghost` — icon-only / close
  - `link` — inline text action

## Crawl actions

- Use [`CrawlActionBar`](resources/js/Components/CrawlActionBar.tsx) everywhere crawl, download, or upload is triggered.
- Do **not** import [`CrawlDropdown`](resources/js/Components/CrawlDropdown.tsx) from pages — it is internal to `CrawlActionBar`.
- Scopes: `account` (Flickr accounts table) or `contact` (contacts list rows, contact detail).

## Cards

- Use [`Card`](resources/js/Components/Card.tsx) for all card layouts.
- Flickr/Storage settings use [`ProviderCard`](resources/js/Components/ProviderCard.tsx) preset — not a separate layout.
